trans-unit.source: Defines a segment of time that may contain child <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline"></xref> objects.
trans-unit.target: Definerer et segment tiden som kan inneholde underordnede <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline"> </xref> objekter.

trans-unit.source: These child timelines become active according to their respective <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime*> properties.
trans-unit.target: Disse underordnede tidslinjer aktiveres i henhold til de respektive <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime*>Egenskaper.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime*>

trans-unit.source: Also, child timelines are able to overlap (run in parallel) with each other.
trans-unit.target: Underordnede tidslinjer vil også kunne overlappe (Kjør i parallelt) med hverandre.

trans-unit.source: ParallelTimeline objects can be children (nested inside) of a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.
trans-unit.target: ParallelTimeline objekter kan være underordnede (nestes i) av <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>

trans-unit.source: This can provide better encapsulation of timing sequences in complex animations.
trans-unit.target: Dette kan gi bedre innkapsling av tidsberegning sekvenser i komplekse animasjoner.

trans-unit.source: ParallelTimeline has its own <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime%2A> property therefore all child timeline <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime%2A> values are relative to the parent ParallelTimeline value for <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime%2A>.
trans-unit.target: ParallelTimeline har sine egne <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime%2A>egenskapen derfor alle underordnede tidslinjen <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime%2A>verdier er i forhold til overordnet ParallelTimeline verdi for <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.BeginTime%2A>

trans-unit.source: Return the natural duration (duration of a single iteration) from a specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.Clock"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer den naturlige varigheten (varighet for en enkelt gjentakelse) fra et angitt <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.Clock"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: A natural duration is the period of a single iteration.
trans-unit.target: En naturlig varighet er perioden for en enkelt gjentakelse.

trans-unit.source: If this method returns <xref:System.Windows.Duration.Automatic%2A> it means that the natural duration is unknown.
trans-unit.target: Hvis denne metoden returnerer <xref:System.Windows.Duration.Automatic%2A>betyr at naturlig varigheten er ukjent.</xref:System.Windows.Duration.Automatic%2A>

trans-unit.source: In this case, the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Clock.NaturalDuration%2A> of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Clock> is determined by the author.
trans-unit.target: I dette tilfellet den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Clock.NaturalDuration%2A>av den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Clock>avgjøres av forfatteren.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Clock> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Clock.NaturalDuration%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, the duration of streaming media would be determined by the provider of the streaming media.
trans-unit.target: Hvor lenge direkteavspilt multimedia ville for eksempel fastslås av leverandøren for direkteavspilt multimedia.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.Clock"></xref> to return the natural duration from.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.Clock"> </xref> til å returnere naturlig varigheten fra.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Windows.Duration"></xref> quantity representing the natural duration.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Windows.Duration"> </xref> antall som representerer naturlig varigheten.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets a value that specifies how this timeline will behave when one or more of its <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline"></xref> children slips.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir en verdi som angir hvordan denne tidslinjen vil fungere når én eller flere av dens <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline"> </xref> underordnede følgesedler.

trans-unit.source: It is often desirable to synchronize animations and media.
trans-unit.target: Det er ofte ønskelig å synkronisere animasjoner og medier.

trans-unit.source: However, this is complicated by the fact that media playback can be delayed by loading or buffering making it difficult to reliably play an animation along with media.
trans-unit.target: Dette er imidlertid komplisert ved at media avspilling kan bli forsinket ved innlasting av eller bufring slik at det er vanskelig å spille en animasjonen sammen med media en pålitelig måte.

trans-unit.source: The SlipBehavior property is used to determine what happens when media and animations are played together.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen SlipBehavior brukes til å finne ut hva som skjer når media og animasjoner spilles sammen.

trans-unit.source: A value of <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior> (default) specifies that animation timelines do not need to be synced and will play when specified regardless of the state of other media in the timeline.
trans-unit.target: Verdien <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior>(standard) angir at animasjonen tidslinjer trenger ikke å synkroniseres og spilles når angitt uansett om andre medier i tidslinjen.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior>

trans-unit.source: A value of <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior> on the other hand, specifies that an animation will wait (slip) until media is ready to play.
trans-unit.target: Verdien <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior>på den andre siden angir at en animasjon venter (liste) til mediet er klar til å spille.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior>

trans-unit.source: The diagrams below illustrate this behavior.
trans-unit.target: Diagrammene nedenfor illustrerer dette problemet.

trans-unit.source: This <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> plays a video and an animation.
trans-unit.target: Dette <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>spilles av en video og en animasjon.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>

trans-unit.source: When SlipBehavior is set to <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior> and the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Duration%2A> property of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> is set to <xref:System.Windows.Duration.Automatic%2A>, the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> grows to play all media and animations.
trans-unit.target: Når SlipBehavior er satt til <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior>og <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Duration%2A>for den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>er satt til <xref:System.Windows.Duration.Automatic%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>blir å spille alle medier og animasjoner.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> </xref:System.Windows.Duration.Automatic%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Duration%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior>

trans-unit.source: ![Diagram: Key for SlipBehavior diagram](~/add/media/slipbehaviorkey.png "Diagram: Key for SlipBehavior diagram") ![Diagram: SlipBehavior property value of Grow](~/add/media/slipbehaviorgrow1.png "Diagram: SlipBehavior property value of Grow") This <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> has a SlipBehavior of <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior> and a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Duration%2A> of 5 seconds which gives media and animations 5 seconds to play regardless of how much they slip.
trans-unit.target: ![Diagrammet: Nøkkel for SlipBehavior diagrammet](~/add/media/slipbehaviorkey.png "diagrammet: nøkkel for SlipBehavior diagrammet")![diagrammet: SlipBehavior egenskapsverdi for Øk](~/add/media/slipbehaviorgrow1.png "diagrammet: SlipBehavior egenskapsverdi for Øk") dette <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>har en SlipBehavior av <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior>og en <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Duration%2A>på 5 sekunder som gir media og animasjoner 5 sekunder for å spille uansett hvor mye de forsinket.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Duration%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>

trans-unit.source: ![Diagram: SlipBehavior property value of Grow](~/add/media/slipbehaviorgrow2.png "Diagram: SlipBehavior property value of Grow") This <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> has a SlipBehavior of <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior>.
trans-unit.target: ![Diagrammet: SlipBehavior egenskapsverdi for Øk](~/add/media/slipbehaviorgrow2.png "diagrammet: SlipBehavior egenskapsverdi for Øk") dette <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>er en SlipBehavior av <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>

trans-unit.source: Note that the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.DoubleAnimation> (and any other non-media children of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>) does not progress unless the media timeline is also progressing.
trans-unit.target: Legg merke til at den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.DoubleAnimation>(og andre ikke media underordnede av den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>) pågår ikke med mindre media tidslinjen pågår også.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.DoubleAnimation>

trans-unit.source: If the media takes a while to load, or if it is buffering, the animation will wait (slips) with it.
trans-unit.target: Hvis mediet tar lang tid å laste inn, eller hvis den er bufring, vent animasjonen (følgesedler) med den.

trans-unit.source: This allows animations to synchronize with a single media file.
trans-unit.target: Dette gjør at animasjoner kan synkronisere med en enkelt media-fil.

trans-unit.source: ![SlipBehavior diagram for media and animation](~/add/media/slipbehaviorslip1.png "SlipBehavior diagram for media and animation") This <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> has a SlipBehavior of <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior> and a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Duration%2A> of 5 seconds.
trans-unit.target: ![SlipBehavior diagrammet for medier og animasjonen](~/add/media/slipbehaviorslip1.png "SlipBehavior diagrammet for medier og animasjonen") dette <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>har en SlipBehavior av <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior>og en <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Duration%2A>på 5 sekunder.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Duration%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.SlipBehavior> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>

trans-unit.source: In this scenario, the media file and animation are guaranteed to play for 5 seconds.
trans-unit.target: I dette scenarioet garanteres media fil- og animasjonen skal spilles 5 sekunder.
